The paper deals with the problem of power allocation in wirelessly-powered sensor networks, which involves channel estimation and energy beamforming. This problem is related to several areas of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, given the focus on wireless communication and signal processing, we believe that cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely categories, followed by cs.SY, cs.MM, and cs.LG.
